title: Pattern Book (Germany), 1760
creditline: Museum purchase from Au Panier Fleuri Fund
description: Weaver's thesis book or manuscript of 200 patterns on 157 leaves executed in pen and ink. Patterns for weaving and embroidery with inscriptions. Geometric, floral, and animal designs.

tombstone.epitaph: Pattern Book (Germany), 1760; leather, paper, metal; H x W x D: 20.5 x 16 cm (8 1/16 x 6 5/16 in.); Museum purchase from Au Panier Fleuri Fund; 1961-123-1
